<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–547: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-05T19:00:00+03:00">April 5,
                                1947—7 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received April 5—12:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1209. <hi rend="smallcaps">Kosmos</hi> 22. For Humelsine<note n="72" xml:id="d640fn1">Carlisle H. Humelsine, Director of the Office of
                            Departmental Administration.</note> from Carter. Look at Department’s
                        suggestion in third paragraph of <hi rend="smallcaps">Moskco</hi> 40<note n="73" xml:id="d640fn2">See telegram No. 773, April 2, 7 p.m., to the
                            Ambassador in the Soviet Union, <ref target="#pg_814">p.
                            814</ref>.</note> re ammunition for China.</p>
                    <p>Before the Secretary considers the matter further, he wishes to know
                        character of public announcement Department would make in case of sale of
                        7.92 mm ammunition.</p>
                    <p>Please wire me complete text of a proposed draft statement to support action
                        Department suggests.</p>
                    <p>Understand clearly matter still completely exploratory. [Carter.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>